WEBVTT

00:00.960 --> 00:08.180
Non è una definizione, ma una regola, che dice che si può chiamare un paese una democrazia

00:08.180 --> 00:12.900
quando ha cambiato il suo governo due volte per le elezioni.

00:13.260 --> 00:14.580
Una volta non è abbastanza.

00:14.780 --> 00:22.160
Abbiamo visto che un governo in potere, sia in principio, sia in advertenza,

00:22.800 --> 00:25.640
può essere votato senza potere.

00:25.640 --> 00:27.880
E quelli che vengono a rimanere il paese,

00:28.260 --> 00:32.760
prendono una buona cura di non partire dalla stessa rotta in cui erano venuti.

00:33.540 --> 00:35.940
Troppo, credo, che lo stabiliscono abbastanza bene.

00:37.760 --> 00:41.220
La democrazia, in questo senso in cui ho definito,

00:42.260 --> 00:47.200
ha una relazionazione molto limitata in storia umana e geografia.

00:47.820 --> 00:53.660
In base, la forma di governo ha funzionato in una regione comparativamente piccola del mondo,

00:53.660 --> 00:55.760
principalmente negli paesi inglesi.

00:56.820 --> 01:01.660
E' stato trasplantato con successo intermitente

01:01.660 --> 01:04.040
al continento dell'Europa,

01:05.140 --> 01:07.660
dove il record è, diciamo, mixato,

01:08.280 --> 01:09.960
e i prospetti anche.

01:10.660 --> 01:15.120
Con in mente le vicissitudini della democrazia europea,

01:15.360 --> 01:17.480
dovremmo essere più tolleranti

01:17.480 --> 01:20.740
delle difficoltà che sono currentemente incontrate

01:20.740 --> 01:25.320
da quelli che stanno cercando di introdurre la democrazia stile occidentale

01:25.320 --> 01:28.400
in circostanti ancora più infamili.

01:30.600 --> 01:34.480
Forse potrei fare il mio punto più chiaro con una semplice analogia

01:35.960 --> 01:40.180
introdotta da un'altra invenzione della stessa fonte,

01:40.760 --> 01:41.620
il gioco del football.

01:42.660 --> 01:46.480
Il football è un gioco in cui due parti contengono

01:46.480 --> 01:49.740
e fanno il loro piacere di vincere,

01:49.900 --> 01:52.220
ma entrambi hanno gli stessi diritti,

01:52.480 --> 01:54.800
entrambi operano sotto le stesse regole,

01:55.200 --> 01:58.440
entrambi sanno che neanche vittoria e non vincere è finale,

01:59.400 --> 02:01.040
e si incontrano per un piatto dopo.

02:04.400 --> 02:06.200
Sì, forse uno potrebbe fare un'altra cosa,

02:06.320 --> 02:07.840
che, anche se ci possono essere molti team,

02:08.040 --> 02:10.960
il gioco è più efficace quando ci sono solo due

02:10.960 --> 02:12.360
nel campo allo stesso tempo.

02:14.640 --> 02:17.300
Andiamo a un altro termine importante,

02:17.740 --> 02:19.820
che, di nuovo, è stato usato un numero di volte

02:19.820 --> 02:21.640
nelle nostre discussioni qui,

02:21.640 --> 02:23.200
il termine fondamentalismo.

02:25.220 --> 02:29.520
Questo è un termine, la storia della quale è conosciuta,

02:29.600 --> 02:33.180
il significato originale della quale è molto specifico.

02:33.420 --> 02:35.360
Il nome fondamentalismo, il vero fondamentalismo,

02:35.980 --> 02:39.280
non è soltanto esterno, è americano-protestante.

02:39.280 --> 02:43.620
È stato usato prima, secondo le lexicografie,

02:43.760 --> 02:45.200
in circa il 1920,

02:46.320 --> 02:49.580
per designare alcune strade americane-protestanti

02:49.580 --> 02:51.280
e per differenziarli

02:51.960 --> 02:54.520
dalla strada principale delle strade protestanti.

02:55.560 --> 02:57.650
Il nome viene da una serie di bokletti

02:58.160 --> 03:00.020
pubblicati da queste strade,

03:00.360 --> 03:02.340
da un clergyman da queste strade,

03:02.700 --> 03:04.570
con la lettera generale, i fondamentali.

03:05.560 --> 03:07.290
Una serie di bokletti chiamati fondamentali,

03:07.290 --> 03:09.710
quindi i fondamentalisti,

03:09.810 --> 03:11.370
quelli che credono su queste principali.

03:12.670 --> 03:15.910
I fondamentalisti differono da la strada principale delle strade protestanti

03:15.910 --> 03:17.290
e, dunque, altri cristiani,

03:18.190 --> 03:19.290
su due punti maggiori.

03:21.470 --> 03:24.330
La teologia liberale e il critico biblico.

03:25.370 --> 03:27.470
Li hanno obbligato fortemente a entrambi.

03:27.850 --> 03:30.170
Erano contro la teologia liberale in tutte le forme

03:30.170 --> 03:34.210
e insistivano sulle textuali divinità

03:34.210 --> 03:36.710
e inerranza della Bibbia.

03:37.910 --> 03:40.290
Ora, in Irlanda,

03:40.470 --> 03:42.750
sono stato accostumato a usare questo termo fondamentalismo

03:43.410 --> 03:46.930
con una lunga range di applicazioni.

03:47.030 --> 03:48.350
E può essere mislevo.

03:49.130 --> 03:50.790
Sto parlando specificamente

03:50.790 --> 03:53.390
di quello chiamato il fondamentalismo islamico.

03:54.810 --> 03:58.730
La teologia liberale è stata un'issue nel passato tra gli islami.

03:59.510 --> 04:02.650
Può essere ancora un'issue nel futuro tra gli islami.

04:03.110 --> 04:05.130
Non è un'issue nel momento presente.

04:05.130 --> 04:07.350
Non è quello a cui stanno parlando.

04:08.950 --> 04:11.870
Per l'inerranza e la divinità della Bibbia

04:11.870 --> 04:13.650
è una dogma basica.

04:14.310 --> 04:15.950
La divinità del Coran,

04:16.130 --> 04:18.130
una che è riconosciuta,

04:19.210 --> 04:22.130
o almeno non è chiamata

04:26.070 --> 04:27.690
da tutti gli islami,

04:28.690 --> 04:29.990
nonostante per il loro credere,

04:30.110 --> 04:30.910
il loro praticare,

04:30.910 --> 04:32.910
o nemmeno acquiescente.

04:35.430 --> 04:37.770
La differenza tra quelli che noi oggi

04:37.770 --> 04:40.430
chiamiamo fondamentali islamici e altri islami

04:40.430 --> 04:42.110
è qualcosa di molto diverso.

04:42.870 --> 04:44.890
È la domanda, basicamente,

04:45.210 --> 04:47.290
della natura islamica del Stato.

04:48.130 --> 04:50.930
È una politica e, a un certo punto,

04:51.050 --> 04:51.970
una differenza sociale.

04:52.970 --> 04:55.250
Il loro movimento è una protesta

04:55.250 --> 04:57.590
contro ciò che vedono

04:57.590 --> 04:59.810
come la deislamizzazione

04:59.810 --> 05:01.450
del Stato e della società

05:01.450 --> 05:02.530
nei paesi islamici

05:02.530 --> 05:05.070
sotto le influenze perniciose, alienanze

05:05.070 --> 05:06.710
e infideli.

05:07.790 --> 05:10.590
E il loro rimedio è la reislamizzazione

05:11.110 --> 05:12.930
del Stato e della società,

05:13.530 --> 05:14.270
in particolare,

05:14.590 --> 05:16.130
con la reimposazione

05:16.130 --> 05:17.870
dell'Islamo Sospetto,

05:17.890 --> 05:19.050
della Sharia,

05:19.230 --> 05:20.730
che gli islami credono

05:20.730 --> 05:23.730
diventare divinissimi e ottenere.

05:27.590 --> 05:28.910
Alcuni hanno protestato

05:28.910 --> 05:30.630
contro l'uso di questo termine,

05:31.010 --> 05:31.130
in particolare,

05:31.370 --> 05:32.190
perché ha avuto

05:32.190 --> 05:33.230
un elemento di pregiudizio,

05:33.230 --> 05:34.670
in particolare,

05:35.090 --> 05:37.070
perché ha avuto

05:37.070 --> 05:39.650
un elemento di pregiudizio,

05:39.930 --> 05:41.650
di condemnation.

05:46.450 --> 05:48.670
In alcuni paesi,

05:49.290 --> 05:51.590
il termine islamismo è usato

05:52.190 --> 05:53.690
e quelli che professano

05:53.690 --> 05:55.710
queste creazioni sono chiamati islamisti.

05:55.710 --> 05:57.390
Questo, a me sembra,

05:57.650 --> 05:59.030
è molto più pericoloso,

05:59.710 --> 06:01.650
perché avrebbe impiato

06:01.650 --> 06:03.110
che questo sia qualcosa di centrale

06:03.110 --> 06:04.850
e tipico dell'islam,

06:05.010 --> 06:07.710
che non è certamente.

06:08.450 --> 06:11.810
Nel francese, il termine integrismo

06:11.810 --> 06:13.390
è usato, in italiano

06:13.390 --> 06:14.890
dico integrismo.

06:16.170 --> 06:17.070
Queste sono di nuovo

06:17.070 --> 06:18.610
termini cristiani westerni,

06:19.670 --> 06:20.890
irrelevanti all'islam,

06:20.890 --> 06:22.590
ma non voglio pronunciare

06:22.590 --> 06:23.670
in francese o in italiano.

06:24.870 --> 06:26.630
Ciò che mi sembra significativo

06:26.630 --> 06:28.270
è che in anni recenti

06:28.270 --> 06:30.130
il termine inglese, il termine

06:30.130 --> 06:32.750
americano-protestante, il termine fondamentalismo

06:32.750 --> 06:34.050
è stato letteralmente,

06:34.440 --> 06:36.650
textualmente traslato in arabic

06:36.650 --> 06:38.690
e persiano e turco

06:38.690 --> 06:40.330
e, non dimenticare, in altre

06:40.330 --> 06:42.610
lingue dell'islam e usato

06:42.610 --> 06:44.530
per designare questi movimenti.

06:45.030 --> 06:46.970
E se gli islamisti usano questo termine

06:46.970 --> 06:48.810
per designare i movimenti islamici,

06:49.290 --> 06:50.790
penso che avremo bisogno

06:50.790 --> 06:52.170
di fare la stessa cosa

06:52.170 --> 06:54.010
e non sentire l'imbarizio.

06:56.450 --> 06:58.930
La mia quarta definizione

06:58.930 --> 07:00.270
è la termina islamica.

07:01.910 --> 07:03.270
È già stata

07:03.270 --> 07:04.790
menzionata molte volte in questo

07:04.790 --> 07:06.230
meeting, e ancora le certe

07:06.790 --> 07:07.970
ambiguità che arrivano.

07:08.750 --> 07:10.790
Per iniziare, c'è una cosa molto ovvia,

07:11.590 --> 07:13.070
ovvia quando è menzionata,

07:13.390 --> 07:15.050
ma non molte volte

07:15.050 --> 07:15.870
osservata,

07:16.530 --> 07:19.010
che è che usiamo in inglese e in altre

07:19.010 --> 07:20.850
lingue, abbiamo già usato il termine

07:20.850 --> 07:23.270
islamo in due sensi diversi.

07:23.890 --> 07:25.070
Lo usiamo come l'equivalente

07:25.070 --> 07:26.190
della cristianità,

07:26.530 --> 07:28.490
cioè il nome di una religione,

07:29.010 --> 07:30.670
e lo usiamo anche come l'equivalente del

07:31.290 --> 07:32.710
cristianismo, cioè

07:32.710 --> 07:33.950
di una civilizzazione, una cultura

07:33.950 --> 07:36.950
storica, un fenomeno, una civilizzazione

07:36.950 --> 07:38.850
che è cresciuta sotto l'egis

07:38.850 --> 07:41.410
di quella religione. Non è necessario

07:41.410 --> 07:42.890
di spiegare a questa audience

07:42.890 --> 07:44.410
la differenza nel significato,

07:44.450 --> 07:46.890
nel scopo tra i due

07:46.890 --> 07:49.310
termini cristianità e cristianità,

07:50.150 --> 07:50.950
è più difficile

07:50.950 --> 07:53.160
spiegare e mantenere la differenza

07:53.610 --> 07:55.100
tra questi due

07:56.330 --> 07:57.670
differenti definizioni

07:57.670 --> 07:59.050
o usaggi del

07:59.050 --> 08:01.290
stesso termine islamo.

08:01.590 --> 08:02.690
L'ultimo professore Marshall

08:02.690 --> 08:04.650
Hodgson della Università di Chicago,

08:05.670 --> 08:07.010
un grande scolaro su la storia islamica

08:07.010 --> 08:08.490
e la civilizzazione,

08:09.450 --> 08:10.850
che ha detto questa distinzione,

08:11.210 --> 08:12.970
ha suggerito che useremo

08:12.970 --> 08:14.430
il termine islamdom

08:14.430 --> 08:16.520
come l'equivalente del cristianismo,

08:17.630 --> 08:18.690
una buona suggerizione,

08:18.750 --> 08:20.170
ma non ha mai accaduto,

08:21.010 --> 08:22.990
e nessuno, inoltre i personali

08:22.990 --> 08:25.050
disibili del prof. Hodgson

08:25.050 --> 08:26.640
hanno mai usato questo termine in inglese,

08:27.370 --> 08:28.730
non so quale l'equivalente

08:28.730 --> 08:30.510
in altre lingue, esattamente

08:30.510 --> 08:32.570
in turca, dove ci sono due

08:32.570 --> 08:34.850
parole da distinguere,

08:35.230 --> 08:36.770
ma non in arabica e altre lingue.

08:38.130 --> 08:39.710
È molto difficile

08:39.710 --> 08:40.590
generalizzare

08:40.590 --> 08:43.230
l'islamo. Stiamo parlando, ricordate,

08:43.230 --> 08:46.490
di più di 14 secoli di storia.

08:46.930 --> 08:47.590
Stiamo parlando

08:47.590 --> 08:49.250
di più di un milione di persone.

08:50.430 --> 08:52.110
Stiamo parlando di 54

08:52.110 --> 08:53.570
stati sovrapposti,

08:54.530 --> 08:55.450
membri dell'organizzazione

08:55.450 --> 08:57.190
dell'Islamo Congresso,

08:57.190 --> 08:59.970
più grandi minorità musulmane

08:59.970 --> 09:01.050
in Cina,

09:01.590 --> 09:03.570
in India, e ora in crescendo

09:04.850 --> 09:06.070
in l'Europa e

09:06.070 --> 09:06.710
le America.

09:08.950 --> 09:09.350
Inoltre,

09:09.810 --> 09:11.230
bisogna fare l'attento.

09:11.230 --> 09:13.690
Let me turn now

09:13.830 --> 09:15.530
to the

09:15.530 --> 09:17.430
relationship between religion

09:17.430 --> 09:18.890
and political culture

09:18.890 --> 09:21.550
and try to

09:21.550 --> 09:23.710
establish some ground rules

09:23.850 --> 09:25.390
which I will

09:25.830 --> 09:27.510
follow in my discussion

09:27.510 --> 09:29.650
of Islam and Islam's

09:29.650 --> 09:31.510
relationship to liberalism,

09:31.670 --> 09:33.150
to democracy, and more generally

09:33.150 --> 09:34.850
to political culture.

09:38.270 --> 09:39.630
In a sense,

09:39.630 --> 09:40.450
the question

09:41.420 --> 09:43.090
is Islam compatible

09:43.440 --> 09:44.710
with liberal democracy

09:44.710 --> 09:46.930
is part of a larger question.

09:47.670 --> 09:49.110
Is religion compatible

09:49.340 --> 09:50.790
with liberal democracy?

09:52.350 --> 09:53.510
Here I think it may be useful

09:53.510 --> 09:55.490
to make a basic distinction

09:55.490 --> 09:57.770
which applies to all

09:57.770 --> 09:59.690
religions. The distinction

09:59.690 --> 10:02.130
between religion in the sense of

10:02.130 --> 10:03.770
belief, conduct,

10:04.390 --> 10:04.850
worship,

10:06.570 --> 10:07.890
and religion in the

10:07.890 --> 10:09.910
sense of an ideology of empowerment

10:09.910 --> 10:11.110
and enforcement.

10:12.730 --> 10:14.010
In this first sense,

10:14.550 --> 10:15.850
religion as a system

10:15.850 --> 10:18.130
of belief, of conduct,

10:18.350 --> 10:20.430
and of worship, in that sense

10:20.430 --> 10:22.030
there seems to me to be no

10:22.030 --> 10:23.570
reason why

10:24.410 --> 10:26.010
any religion in those

10:26.010 --> 10:27.850
terms should be incompatible

10:27.850 --> 10:29.810
with liberal democracy,

10:29.930 --> 10:31.890
nor indeed with any form of government

10:31.890 --> 10:33.510
that is not in itself

10:33.510 --> 10:35.250
inherently evil.

10:36.370 --> 10:37.710
Such have existed

10:37.710 --> 10:39.610
as we know, as we were recently

10:39.610 --> 10:41.590
reminded. In the other

10:41.590 --> 10:43.530
sense, religion as

10:43.530 --> 10:45.330
an ideology of empowerment, that

10:45.330 --> 10:47.010
of course is another matter.

10:54.350 --> 10:55.770
I think it may be useful

10:57.470 --> 10:58.590
to point

10:58.590 --> 10:59.550
to what seems to me

10:59.550 --> 11:01.030
to be the main differences

11:02.110 --> 11:03.510
between the Christian

11:03.510 --> 11:06.110
Jewish and Islamic

11:06.110 --> 11:06.770
approaches.

11:08.270 --> 11:09.510
And I would like to do so

11:09.510 --> 11:11.570
in terms of what, without intending any

11:11.570 --> 11:13.470
disrespect, I would call the founding

11:13.470 --> 11:14.930
myths of the three religions.

11:17.010 --> 11:17.410
Moses,

11:17.410 --> 11:19.550
you will recall, was not

11:19.550 --> 11:21.730
permitted to enter the promised land.

11:23.050 --> 11:23.510
And

11:23.510 --> 11:25.410
the Hebrew Bible, the

11:25.410 --> 11:26.210
Old Testament,

11:28.150 --> 11:29.590
is dominated by the

11:29.590 --> 11:31.570
two themes of

11:31.570 --> 11:32.970
bondage and liberation

11:33.510 --> 11:35.810
of exile and return.

11:38.050 --> 11:39.250
Jesus was crucified

11:39.250 --> 11:41.570
and his followers survived

11:41.570 --> 11:43.690
as a persecuted minority

11:43.690 --> 11:45.310
for centuries

11:45.310 --> 11:47.430
before finally

11:47.430 --> 11:48.910
converting the state

11:49.210 --> 11:51.570
and inaugurating the processes of

11:52.230 --> 11:53.510
the Christianization

11:53.510 --> 11:55.870
of Rome, and some would add the Romanization

11:55.870 --> 11:56.530
of Christ.

11:58.390 --> 11:59.430
The founding

11:59.430 --> 12:01.550
story of Islam is very different.

12:02.530 --> 12:03.470
The Prophet Muhammad

12:03.470 --> 12:05.370
conquered his promised land

12:05.370 --> 12:07.550
and established a state,

12:07.850 --> 12:09.410
a polity of which he was chief.

12:10.510 --> 12:11.690
Not he, but some of his

12:11.690 --> 12:13.050
enemies were put to death.

12:14.250 --> 12:15.450
And his scripture

12:15.450 --> 12:17.090
tells the story

12:18.130 --> 12:19.650
first of a struggle

12:19.650 --> 12:21.570
to attain power, and

12:21.570 --> 12:23.350
then of the exercise of power.

12:23.890 --> 12:25.650
Muhammad created the first

12:25.650 --> 12:27.570
Muslim state in Medina

12:27.570 --> 12:29.430
and he was the head of it.

12:29.470 --> 12:31.590
And he did what heads of state do.

12:32.890 --> 12:33.850
He dispensed

12:33.850 --> 12:35.570
he promulgated

12:35.570 --> 12:37.310
laws, he dispensed

12:37.310 --> 12:39.490
justice, he collected taxes,

12:40.710 --> 12:41.610
he made war,

12:41.670 --> 12:43.690
he made peace. In other words, he acted

12:43.690 --> 12:45.330
as a political sovereign.

12:47.230 --> 12:48.430
And the

12:48.430 --> 12:49.530
the record, the memories

12:49.530 --> 12:51.650
of his sovereign acts as well as

12:51.650 --> 12:53.010
of his prophetic mission

12:53.570 --> 12:55.690
are part of the central

12:55.690 --> 12:57.790
core of self awareness

12:57.790 --> 12:59.830
of Muslims everywhere

12:59.830 --> 13:00.870
in the world.

13:02.590 --> 13:03.930
And that I think is a very

13:03.930 --> 13:05.790
very important, indeed a

13:05.790 --> 13:06.790
crucial difference

13:07.690 --> 13:09.890
in the Muslim

13:11.070 --> 13:11.910
attitude

13:11.910 --> 13:13.930
to politics in general

13:13.930 --> 13:16.110
and to the conduct of government in particular.

13:16.650 --> 13:17.710
A subject which I should

13:17.710 --> 13:19.730
add is much discussed

13:19.730 --> 13:21.890
in Muslim religious

13:21.890 --> 13:23.410
and legal literature.

13:26.150 --> 13:27.990
There is

13:27.990 --> 13:29.830
a Muslim political

13:29.830 --> 13:30.350
culture.

13:32.030 --> 13:33.810
Indeed, one may speak of

13:33.810 --> 13:35.730
several Muslim political cultures.

13:36.730 --> 13:38.030
If one wants to look

13:38.030 --> 13:40.190
at the compatibility of Christianity

13:40.190 --> 13:41.570
and democracy,

13:42.310 --> 13:43.810
one has I think to take three or

13:43.810 --> 13:45.810
perhaps more accurately four different

13:45.810 --> 13:47.590
varieties. Again,

13:47.770 --> 13:49.690
I am not concerned with

13:50.770 --> 13:51.470
theological

13:51.470 --> 13:53.730
or philosophical or theoretical

13:53.730 --> 13:55.670
statements of any kind

13:55.670 --> 13:57.350
on this particular point,

13:57.890 --> 13:59.370
merely with the historical record.

14:00.290 --> 14:01.830
If you look at the historical

14:01.830 --> 14:03.730
record of the

14:05.830 --> 14:08.170
attempts to run democratic societies

14:08.170 --> 14:09.790
in countries of Orthodox,

14:10.130 --> 14:11.530
of Catholic and of Protestant

14:11.530 --> 14:13.910
Christianity, you would I think be able

14:13.910 --> 14:15.610
to draw up an interesting comparative

14:15.610 --> 14:17.530
table. I said

14:17.530 --> 14:19.170
four rather than three.

14:19.950 --> 14:21.390
The fourth I would call the

14:21.390 --> 14:22.950
post-Christian society.

14:23.590 --> 14:25.210
I would remind you

14:25.210 --> 14:27.750
that secularism is a Christian notion.

14:28.710 --> 14:29.370
Secularism

14:29.370 --> 14:31.990
is a post-Christian

14:31.990 --> 14:33.330
answer to a Christian

14:33.330 --> 14:35.530
dilemma, one which

14:35.530 --> 14:37.170
is posed in the Gospels,

14:37.290 --> 14:38.730
the dilemma of God and Caesar

14:39.150 --> 14:41.290
and which continued to haunt

14:41.290 --> 14:43.250
Christians throughout the history of

14:43.250 --> 14:43.690
Christianity.

14:44.870 --> 14:47.130
That particular dilemma was not a problem

14:47.130 --> 14:49.670
for Muslims. The very notion

14:49.670 --> 14:51.830
of secularism,

14:52.230 --> 14:53.390
of laity,

14:53.830 --> 14:54.970
of totally alien.

14:56.170 --> 14:57.930
Arabic is a Christian as well as

14:57.930 --> 14:59.700
a Muslim language. There are large

15:00.190 --> 15:01.770
words, large and important

15:01.770 --> 15:03.950
Christian communities of Arabic

15:03.950 --> 15:05.670
speech and a considerable Arabic

15:06.390 --> 15:07.390
Christian literature.

15:08.470 --> 15:09.910
So the Arabs did have an advantage

15:09.910 --> 15:12.010
over the Persians and Turks and other peoples

15:12.010 --> 15:13.670
in that they had a Christian vocabulary

15:13.670 --> 15:15.230
available to them in their language.

15:15.850 --> 15:17.810
So there was a word for secular

15:17.810 --> 15:19.850
in Arabic. There was none

15:19.850 --> 15:21.770
in Persian or Turkish. They had to invent

15:21.770 --> 15:22.850
them.

15:23.930 --> 15:25.650
Laity is again an alien

15:25.650 --> 15:27.850
notion. The idea

15:27.850 --> 15:30.130
that some things are

15:30.130 --> 15:31.810
clerical, others are lay is a

15:31.810 --> 15:33.890
Christian notion of very little relevance.

15:42.410 --> 15:44.070
A point I think is very important

15:44.070 --> 15:45.130
to emphasize

15:45.130 --> 15:47.350
is that these three religions,

15:47.910 --> 15:49.630
Judaism, Christianity,

15:50.230 --> 15:51.630
Islam, are closely

15:51.630 --> 15:52.270
related.

15:53.470 --> 15:55.470
If one compares them with the

15:55.470 --> 15:57.370
great religions of Asia, with

15:57.370 --> 15:59.070
Buddhism, Hinduism,

15:59.230 --> 16:01.270
the religions of the Far East, they

16:01.270 --> 16:03.190
are as alike as peas in a pod.

16:04.250 --> 16:05.310
From a larger

16:05.310 --> 16:07.130
perspective, one would I say,

16:07.330 --> 16:09.370
one might I say regard these

16:09.370 --> 16:11.330
as variants of

16:11.330 --> 16:13.330
the same basic religious tradition.

16:13.330 --> 16:15.310
That is I think nowadays

16:15.870 --> 16:17.690
partly at least recognized.

16:18.410 --> 16:19.510
Several speakers in the

16:19.510 --> 16:21.550
last couple of days have used the term

16:21.550 --> 16:23.330
the Judeo-Christian tradition

16:23.330 --> 16:24.990
or Judeo-Christian religion.

16:26.310 --> 16:27.510
This is an old reality

16:27.510 --> 16:28.870
but a very modern term.

16:29.750 --> 16:31.390
Before the present century, it would have

16:31.390 --> 16:33.790
been found offensive on both sides of the hyphen.

16:35.110 --> 16:35.550
Nowadays

16:35.550 --> 16:37.350
it's passed into common

16:37.350 --> 16:39.510
usage on both sides

16:39.510 --> 16:41.750
of the hyphen. One could of course

16:41.750 --> 16:43.450
though one doesn't usually speak

16:43.450 --> 16:45.630
with equal justification of a

16:45.630 --> 16:47.070
Judeo-Islamic tradition.

16:48.230 --> 16:50.090
Jewish life in the period between

16:50.090 --> 16:51.870
the destruction of the ancient Jewish

16:51.870 --> 16:53.570
polity and the creation of the modern

16:53.570 --> 16:55.590
Jewish polity was passed

16:55.590 --> 16:57.910
mainly in the lands of Christendom

16:57.910 --> 16:58.830
and of Islam.

16:59.730 --> 17:01.570
The Jewish experience outside

17:01.570 --> 17:03.590
these two is insignificant.

17:04.810 --> 17:05.830
And there is a

17:05.830 --> 17:07.730
Judeo-Islamic tradition just

17:07.730 --> 17:09.870
as there is a Judeo-Christian tradition.

17:09.870 --> 17:12.040
One of the more interesting

17:12.430 --> 17:14.030
things about the modern state of

17:14.030 --> 17:15.990
Israel is that therefore the first

17:15.990 --> 17:17.330
time in many centuries

17:17.760 --> 17:19.980
the Judeo-Christian and the Judeo-Islamic

17:21.450 --> 17:22.510
traditions meet

17:22.510 --> 17:24.230
in the same state

17:24.230 --> 17:26.030
and one sees the great

17:26.030 --> 17:28.050
differences between them

17:28.950 --> 17:29.930
almost a

17:29.930 --> 17:31.950
laboratory controlled experiment

17:31.950 --> 17:33.910
on the larger encounter of

17:33.910 --> 17:34.970
Christendom and Islam.

17:36.670 --> 17:37.850
This kinship

17:37.850 --> 17:39.790
between Christianity and Islam and

17:39.790 --> 17:40.170
Judaism

17:41.610 --> 17:44.230
has made communication

17:44.230 --> 17:44.930
possible.

17:45.870 --> 17:47.630
We find for example in the Middle Ages

17:47.630 --> 17:49.910
in Spain, in Sicily and elsewhere

17:49.910 --> 17:52.110
Christians and Muslims engaging

17:52.110 --> 17:53.570
in disputations,

17:54.010 --> 17:55.470
theological disputations.

17:56.310 --> 17:58.050
This was possible because both

17:58.050 --> 17:59.750
were speaking the same language

17:59.750 --> 18:01.950
figuratively as well as literally

18:01.950 --> 18:04.230
talking about the same things.

18:04.690 --> 18:05.970
Such a disputation would have

18:05.970 --> 18:07.810
made impossible with a Hindu or a Buddhist

18:07.810 --> 18:09.730
or a Confucian, there would have been no common

18:09.730 --> 18:10.230
language.

18:12.050 --> 18:13.550
When Christians and Muslims

18:13.550 --> 18:16.090
denounced each other as infidels

18:16.090 --> 18:18.390
each knew exactly what they meant

18:18.390 --> 18:20.030
because they meant the same thing.

18:20.570 --> 18:22.110
When Christians and Muslims said to

18:22.110 --> 18:24.050
each other you are an unbeliever and you will

18:24.050 --> 18:26.150
burn in hell, again

18:26.150 --> 18:27.970
both understood what the other

18:27.970 --> 18:30.090
meant because both meant precisely the same

18:30.090 --> 18:31.990
thing. Their heavens are

18:31.990 --> 18:33.770
somewhat different but their hells are almost

18:33.770 --> 18:34.190
identical.

18:38.990 --> 18:40.630
All that by way of

18:40.630 --> 18:42.130
introduction to explain

18:42.130 --> 18:43.910
some of the terms that I am using.

18:44.070 --> 18:46.110
I want to turn now to a more

18:46.110 --> 18:48.390
specific examination of Islam

18:48.390 --> 18:50.230
in relation

18:50.230 --> 18:51.990
to liberalism,

18:52.390 --> 18:53.710
democracy, liberal democracy,

18:53.910 --> 18:56.250
whatever and to consider

18:56.250 --> 18:57.850
first those elements

18:57.850 --> 18:59.950
in Islamic civilization, in Islamic

18:59.950 --> 19:02.050
history which would militate

19:02.050 --> 19:03.970
against the success

19:05.110 --> 19:06.210
of democracy

19:06.210 --> 19:07.930
in Islamic lands and then

19:07.930 --> 19:10.490
since I prefer to end on an optimistic note

19:10.490 --> 19:12.150
then those that

19:12.150 --> 19:14.310
are more positive and more favourable.

19:15.490 --> 19:16.090
The first and

19:16.090 --> 19:17.990
most obvious one is the

19:17.990 --> 19:20.410
unmistakable authoritarianism

19:20.410 --> 19:21.730
of the Islamic

19:21.730 --> 19:23.250
political tradition.

19:24.230 --> 19:26.030
An authoritarianism which it shares

19:26.030 --> 19:27.930
of course with most of Christendom

19:27.930 --> 19:29.570
for most of Christian history

19:29.570 --> 19:31.590
but which in the case of Islam

19:31.590 --> 19:33.530
is almost completely

19:33.530 --> 19:34.790
unrelieved.

19:35.690 --> 19:37.610
This authoritarianism is both

19:37.610 --> 19:39.010
historic and doctrinal.

19:39.770 --> 19:41.930
If we look at the record of Muslim states

19:41.930 --> 19:44.030
we find that authoritarian

19:44.030 --> 19:45.290
rule is the norm.

19:46.030 --> 19:47.490
If we look at the 54

19:47.490 --> 19:49.650
Muslim states at the present time

19:51.510 --> 19:53.190
the vast majority

19:53.190 --> 19:55.810
are authoritarian in one

19:55.810 --> 19:56.870
form or another.

19:56.870 --> 19:59.140
Only one of them

20:00.230 --> 20:01.710
remotely qualifies

20:01.710 --> 20:03.530
as a democracy

20:03.530 --> 20:05.230
by Huntington's definition

20:05.230 --> 20:07.250
of having changed the government twice

20:07.250 --> 20:09.310
by elections, that is the Turkish

20:09.310 --> 20:11.220
Republic and that is

20:11.490 --> 20:13.250
still a very troubled

20:13.250 --> 20:15.030
democracy, although it does

20:15.030 --> 20:16.570
change governments by elections.

20:17.910 --> 20:19.290
There is also a

20:19.290 --> 20:20.870
doctrinal authoritarianism

20:21.430 --> 20:23.070
in the very notion

20:23.070 --> 20:25.410
of holy law, of a divine

20:25.410 --> 20:27.410
law, revealed,

20:27.910 --> 20:29.670
formulated, promulgated

20:29.670 --> 20:31.430
which regulates not

20:31.430 --> 20:33.510
only those things which in

20:33.510 --> 20:35.390
other religions might be regarded as

20:35.390 --> 20:37.390
specifically religious but

20:37.390 --> 20:39.790
also every aspect

20:40.050 --> 20:41.190
of life

20:41.190 --> 20:43.010
and more particularly

20:43.010 --> 20:45.390
such things as marriage, divorce,

20:45.710 --> 20:47.250
inheritance, family life

20:47.250 --> 20:49.630
and the rest and of course

20:49.630 --> 20:51.390
the conduct of the state.

20:52.690 --> 20:54.090
That is not

20:54.090 --> 20:56.150
very conducive to the development

20:56.150 --> 20:58.130
of liberal institutions or democratic

20:58.130 --> 21:00.090
ways. The earliest

21:00.090 --> 21:02.050
description of England

21:02.050 --> 21:03.650
that we have,

21:04.010 --> 21:05.470
the earliest that is to say in any

21:05.470 --> 21:07.690
detail, is a Muslim

21:07.690 --> 21:09.570
from Lucknow who visited

21:09.570 --> 21:11.610
England in 1798.

21:12.710 --> 21:13.630
He was of Persian

21:13.630 --> 21:15.390
background and wrote a book in Persian

21:15.390 --> 21:17.510
a fascinating account of England and

21:17.510 --> 21:19.570
France and

21:19.570 --> 21:21.770
one of the places his hosts took him to

21:21.770 --> 21:23.150
was the House of Commons

21:23.710 --> 21:25.570
and this he tries to explain

21:25.570 --> 21:27.230
to his readers back home.

21:27.770 --> 21:29.730
He begins with a rather unflattering comparison.

21:30.110 --> 21:31.590
He describes the two sides

21:31.590 --> 21:33.610
of the house and says this

21:33.610 --> 21:35.810
is like what one often sees in India

21:35.810 --> 21:37.170
two trees

21:37.170 --> 21:39.730
on opposite sides of the road both full of

21:39.730 --> 21:41.550
parrots squawking at each other.

21:43.250 --> 21:45.790
But then he goes on to explain what this is for

21:45.790 --> 21:47.590
and he explains that

21:47.590 --> 21:49.550
the poor benighted English

21:49.550 --> 21:51.730
unlike the Muslims had never

21:51.730 --> 21:53.230
accepted a divine law

21:53.230 --> 21:56.030
and were therefore reduced to the expedient

21:56.030 --> 21:57.510
of making their own laws

21:57.510 --> 21:59.670
in accordance with the experience

21:59.670 --> 22:01.710
of their judges and the necessities

22:01.710 --> 22:03.690
of the moment, which he regards

22:03.690 --> 22:05.590
obviously as a very

22:06.350 --> 22:08.010
poor expedient

22:08.010 --> 22:08.850
the people

22:09.480 --> 22:11.210
who have denied themselves

22:11.210 --> 22:13.870
this major benefit of divine

22:13.870 --> 22:14.490
guidance.

22:15.490 --> 22:17.890
That system you don't need

22:17.890 --> 22:19.230
a legislative assembly

22:19.970 --> 22:21.410
and that of course

22:21.410 --> 22:22.820
has far reaching implications.

22:24.970 --> 22:27.010
Another factor against linked to this

22:27.010 --> 22:28.450
is the triumphalism.

22:28.850 --> 22:31.030
The belief which Islam shares

22:31.030 --> 22:33.030
with Christianity and as far as I know

22:33.030 --> 22:34.210
with no other religion

22:34.210 --> 22:36.620
are being the final possessor

22:37.210 --> 22:38.330
of God's truth

22:38.330 --> 22:40.870
which it is therefore their

22:40.870 --> 22:42.970
sacred duty to bring to others.

22:42.970 --> 22:45.350
This again makes

22:46.150 --> 22:47.410
the interchange

22:47.410 --> 22:48.970
and exchange

22:48.970 --> 22:51.410
of democratic life more difficult.

22:52.850 --> 22:54.970
One of the most serious

22:56.290 --> 22:56.930
obstructions

22:56.930 --> 22:59.010
is the position of women.

23:01.750 --> 23:03.330
The first who raised this as a

23:03.330 --> 23:04.990
major issue as far as I am aware

23:04.990 --> 23:07.170
in a Muslim country was

23:07.170 --> 23:09.090
Kamal Atatürk who again has

23:09.090 --> 23:10.950
been mentioned several times at these

23:10.950 --> 23:12.930
meetings, the founder

23:12.930 --> 23:14.270
and first president

23:14.850 --> 23:16.190
of the Turkish Republic,

23:17.250 --> 23:18.870
an Ottoman Pasha and a military

23:18.870 --> 23:20.830
general, an improbable feminist.

23:22.170 --> 23:22.770
Nevertheless

23:22.770 --> 23:24.910
he was the first to

23:24.910 --> 23:27.210
proclaim the need for the emancipation

23:27.210 --> 23:29.290
of women and the giving of political

23:29.290 --> 23:30.490
rights to women.

23:31.730 --> 23:32.250
He said

23:32.850 --> 23:34.990
several times in a series of speeches

23:34.990 --> 23:36.990
which he delivered in Anatolia in the early

23:37.890 --> 23:38.950
1920s, he said

23:38.950 --> 23:40.050
that our present task

23:40.050 --> 23:42.190
is to catch up with the modern world.

23:42.990 --> 23:44.610
We will not catch up with the modern

23:44.610 --> 23:46.810
world if we only modernize half

23:46.810 --> 23:47.710
the population.

23:49.430 --> 23:50.570
A point which he understood

23:50.570 --> 23:52.710
which many others still have

23:52.710 --> 23:54.710
difficulty in understanding.

23:55.910 --> 23:56.930
If we look at

23:56.930 --> 23:58.910
the accounts of the West

23:58.910 --> 24:00.490
written by Muslim travelers

24:01.390 --> 24:03.090
this is the point on which

24:03.650 --> 24:04.870
almost all seem

24:04.870 --> 24:06.930
to agree the astonishing

24:06.930 --> 24:08.670
to them freedom

24:08.670 --> 24:10.570
accorded to women in Western

24:10.570 --> 24:12.190
and Christian society.

24:13.390 --> 24:14.810
Obviously the position of women

24:14.810 --> 24:16.930
was very far from one of equality in the

24:16.930 --> 24:18.790
West but it was incomparably

24:18.790 --> 24:20.790
better than in most other parts of the world.

24:21.350 --> 24:22.750
One that I find particularly

24:24.190 --> 24:24.710
instructive

24:24.710 --> 24:26.930
is a report from a Moroccan ambassador

24:26.930 --> 24:28.670
in Spain in the late

24:28.670 --> 24:31.010
17th century who comments

24:31.010 --> 24:33.010
on the free and easy ways

24:33.010 --> 24:35.010
of Spanish ladies and the lack

24:35.010 --> 24:37.110
of manly jealousy of Spanish men.

24:37.890 --> 24:38.870
This is Spain

24:38.870 --> 24:41.270
of all places in the late

24:41.270 --> 24:42.210
17th century.

24:43.170 --> 24:45.030
His report on Spain doesn't tell us much

24:45.030 --> 24:46.930
about Spain but he tells us quite a lot about

24:46.930 --> 24:47.330
Morocco.

24:50.970 --> 24:52.770
One of the major reasons

24:52.770 --> 24:55.130
for the relative backwardness of

24:55.130 --> 24:57.150
Islam is surely this

24:57.150 --> 24:59.570
point. If a society

24:59.570 --> 25:00.750
persists

25:00.750 --> 25:03.130
in depriving itself of

25:03.130 --> 25:05.450
the talents and services of half the population

25:05.450 --> 25:07.190
and of entrusting

25:07.190 --> 25:08.850
the nurture of the other half

25:08.850 --> 25:11.210
to uneducated and down trodden

25:11.210 --> 25:13.110
mothers, it will not be able

25:13.110 --> 25:14.690
to keep up with the modern world

25:14.690 --> 25:17.350
nor will it be able to operate any

25:17.350 --> 25:18.930
kind of free

25:18.930 --> 25:20.870
liberal democratic society.

25:21.650 --> 25:23.130
This is increasingly understood

25:25.270 --> 25:26.350
not always

25:27.090 --> 25:29.310
not only I should say

25:29.310 --> 25:31.550
by women, there are there as elsewhere

25:31.550 --> 25:33.550
some women who prefer subordination

25:34.470 --> 25:35.830
but I feel

25:35.830 --> 25:37.690
myself that women who are

25:37.690 --> 25:40.030
after all slightly more than half the population

25:40.030 --> 25:41.570
may yet constitute

25:41.570 --> 25:43.450
the best hope for liberal democracy

25:43.450 --> 25:45.230
in the Islamic world.

25:47.350 --> 25:49.830
I have already mentioned the lack of a legislative

25:49.830 --> 25:51.550
power and therefore the

25:52.350 --> 25:53.490
absence of any need

25:53.490 --> 25:55.070
for a legislative assembly.

25:58.970 --> 25:59.850
One could add

25:59.850 --> 26:01.810
to that the difficulties

26:02.930 --> 26:04.430
arising, this may seem

26:04.430 --> 26:06.170
to you an odd formulation but I stand

26:06.170 --> 26:07.910
by it, difficulties arising

26:07.910 --> 26:09.790
at the present time from oil.

26:11.170 --> 26:12.150
Oil has

26:12.150 --> 26:14.350
enormously enriched some

26:14.350 --> 26:15.710
Muslim governments.

26:16.810 --> 26:17.990
It has freed them

26:17.990 --> 26:20.310
from the need to raise taxes.

26:21.610 --> 26:22.170
It has

26:22.170 --> 26:23.870
freed them therefore from the need

26:23.870 --> 26:26.190
to enter into a dialogue with their subjects.

26:27.110 --> 26:28.150
It has provided

26:28.150 --> 26:30.390
resources to maintain tyranny

26:30.390 --> 26:32.050
at home and terrorism abroad

26:32.050 --> 26:34.450
and in the long run it may well

26:34.450 --> 26:35.950
prove to be a great curse

26:35.950 --> 26:37.470
rather than a blessing.

26:38.090 --> 26:40.130
And it is surely not without

26:40.130 --> 26:42.370
significance that the most hopeful

26:42.370 --> 26:44.010
signs of development

26:44.010 --> 26:45.830
towards a freer society

26:45.830 --> 26:48.250
occur in countries like

26:48.250 --> 26:50.130
Tunisia and Jordan

26:51.150 --> 26:52.530
and Turkey

26:52.530 --> 26:54.010
which have no oil.

26:56.770 --> 26:58.130
Another difficulty

26:58.130 --> 26:59.790
is the absence in

26:59.790 --> 27:01.830
Muslim law of what in

27:01.830 --> 27:03.650
Roman law is called the legal

27:03.650 --> 27:04.270
person.

27:05.230 --> 27:06.390
There are only individuals.

27:06.570 --> 27:08.910
There is no city, just an accumulation

27:08.910 --> 27:10.210
of quarters and houses.

27:10.730 --> 27:12.490
There is no abstract

27:12.490 --> 27:14.810
legal, no corporate legal

27:14.810 --> 27:15.310
entity.

27:15.950 --> 27:17.650
This is an alien notion.

27:18.970 --> 27:20.370
Therefore no form

27:20.370 --> 27:22.590
of representation, no

27:22.590 --> 27:24.330
form of majority decision.

27:24.930 --> 27:26.650
In the past this didn't matter

27:26.650 --> 27:29.090
but in trying to create

27:29.090 --> 27:30.590
liberal democratic

27:30.590 --> 27:32.750
institutions the absence

27:32.750 --> 27:34.590
of such a tradition is

27:34.590 --> 27:36.230
a serious obstacle.

27:37.110 --> 27:38.570
It's an obstacle which is now

27:38.570 --> 27:40.170
increasingly being overcome

27:40.170 --> 27:42.570
as the modern economy

27:42.570 --> 27:44.710
has created the need for

27:44.710 --> 27:46.550
such institutions and such

27:46.550 --> 27:47.030
laws.

27:49.010 --> 27:50.990
Let me turn now to

27:50.990 --> 27:52.750
what seem to me to be the factors

27:52.750 --> 27:54.990
in Islam which

27:54.990 --> 27:57.010
are conducive to the

27:57.010 --> 27:58.970
development of liberal

27:58.970 --> 27:59.610
democracy.

28:01.170 --> 28:03.190
The first and most important of these

28:03.770 --> 28:04.970
of the political

28:04.970 --> 28:07.050
factors is the

28:07.050 --> 28:08.450
Muslim doctrine of sovereignty.

28:09.150 --> 28:11.110
This is a subject which is

28:11.110 --> 28:12.530
widely discussed

28:15.290 --> 28:16.130
by

28:16.130 --> 28:17.070
jurists

28:17.070 --> 28:19.290
and theologians in Islam

28:19.290 --> 28:21.310
going back a very long way.

28:23.670 --> 28:24.950
And the

28:24.950 --> 28:25.590
supreme

28:25.590 --> 28:27.410
institution of sovereignty is the

28:27.410 --> 28:29.330
caliphate and there is much

28:29.330 --> 28:31.630
discussion as to how one becomes caliph

28:31.630 --> 28:33.170
and what one's duties are.

28:34.190 --> 28:35.450
And a reading of these

28:35.450 --> 28:36.850
texts makes it quite clear

28:36.850 --> 28:39.090
that according to Muslim doctrine

28:39.090 --> 28:41.350
the supreme sovereign office

28:42.730 --> 28:44.010
is contractual

28:44.010 --> 28:45.290
and consensual.

28:46.430 --> 28:47.490
The caliph becomes

28:47.490 --> 28:49.070
caliph by a contract

28:49.070 --> 28:50.810
between him and his subjects.

28:51.530 --> 28:53.710
A contract which imposes duties

28:53.710 --> 28:55.210
as well as giving

28:55.210 --> 28:57.270
rights to the ruler.

28:58.110 --> 28:59.750
And it is consensual

28:59.750 --> 29:01.450
in that it depends

29:01.450 --> 29:03.430
on the consent of the ruled.

29:04.190 --> 29:05.590
Now you might say this is

29:05.590 --> 29:07.690
theoretical, this isn't how it actually happened.

29:08.230 --> 29:09.530
This would be a

29:09.530 --> 29:11.430
valid, though not entirely valid

29:11.430 --> 29:13.710
criticism. In that generally

29:13.710 --> 29:15.670
speaking certain minimal

29:15.670 --> 29:17.150
norms were observed.

29:17.930 --> 29:19.830
It is rare in Islamic history

29:19.830 --> 29:21.910
that you find a complete despotism.

29:22.530 --> 29:23.790
You find authoritarian

29:23.790 --> 29:25.750
rule certainly, but

29:25.750 --> 29:28.330
not unprincipled, unrestricted

29:28.330 --> 29:29.370
despotic rule.

29:29.830 --> 29:31.390
It is true that the law gives

29:31.390 --> 29:33.570
authoritarian, gives autocratic powers

29:33.570 --> 29:35.470
to the ruler, but it nevertheless

29:35.470 --> 29:37.270
defines those powers.

29:38.410 --> 29:39.890
An oft cited tradition

29:39.890 --> 29:41.710
of the prophet, as well as

29:41.710 --> 29:43.850
the Qur'an, Muslims believe in the traditions

29:43.850 --> 29:46.070
of the prophet, these are sayings of the prophet

29:46.070 --> 29:47.890
handed down by oral tradition.

29:48.610 --> 29:49.930
A much quoted tradition

29:49.930 --> 29:51.850
of the prophet is

29:51.850 --> 29:54.090
there is no obedience in sin.

29:55.090 --> 29:55.890
That means

29:55.890 --> 29:57.650
that the duty of obedience

29:57.650 --> 29:59.610
which the subject owes to the ruler

30:00.490 --> 30:01.910
lapses when the ruler

30:01.910 --> 30:04.050
orders something that is sinful.

30:04.830 --> 30:05.610
And in that case

30:05.610 --> 30:07.830
duty of obedience is replaced not

30:07.830 --> 30:09.770
by a right of disobedience as in western

30:09.770 --> 30:11.850
political thought, but by a duty

30:11.850 --> 30:12.930
of disobedience.

30:13.610 --> 30:16.290
Of course, there is no constitutional

30:16.290 --> 30:17.790
procedure to decide

30:17.790 --> 30:20.050
when a command is sinful.

30:20.830 --> 30:22.010
That is left to

30:22.010 --> 30:23.810
what we might tactfully call

30:23.810 --> 30:26.190
the play of historical forces.

30:27.790 --> 30:30.110
But the notion is there, the principle is there

30:30.110 --> 30:32.130
and it has increasingly been

30:32.130 --> 30:33.870
cited in modern times

30:33.870 --> 30:35.750
by Muslim dissidents

30:35.750 --> 30:36.910
of various kinds.

30:39.770 --> 30:40.890
Some reference

30:40.890 --> 30:42.310
was made this morning

30:42.310 --> 30:43.910
to tolerance.

30:44.910 --> 30:45.690
Professor Baudet

30:45.690 --> 30:47.130
spoke very rightly

30:47.130 --> 30:50.150
of the inadequacy of tolerance

30:50.150 --> 30:51.950
as a notion in our time.

30:53.070 --> 30:54.050
There is a letter

30:54.050 --> 30:55.150
of George Washington

30:55.150 --> 30:57.810
addressed to the leader of the Jewish community

30:57.810 --> 30:59.310
in Newport, Rhode Island,

30:59.770 --> 31:01.650
in which he says, I'm quoting from memory

31:01.650 --> 31:02.770
but I think accurately,

31:03.550 --> 31:05.130
he says, let us no longer speak of

31:05.130 --> 31:07.130
toleration as if it were

31:07.130 --> 31:09.550
by the indulgence of one group of people

31:09.550 --> 31:10.890
that others enjoy

31:10.890 --> 31:13.190
the exercise of their inherent

31:13.190 --> 31:14.430
natural rights.

31:16.930 --> 31:19.210
That is just over 200 years ago.

31:20.170 --> 31:21.310
It is still not

31:21.310 --> 31:22.190
generally accepted.

31:23.130 --> 31:25.370
In saying that though, I think we should bear in mind

31:25.370 --> 31:27.210
the very real tolerance

31:29.330 --> 31:31.030
exercised by Muslim governments

31:31.030 --> 31:33.290
at a time when this was very far from being

31:33.290 --> 31:33.910
the norm.

31:35.550 --> 31:37.270
The evolution of tolerance in

31:37.270 --> 31:39.370
Christian societies was slow,

31:39.510 --> 31:41.570
difficult, and reluctant.

31:42.590 --> 31:43.370
Christian states

31:43.370 --> 31:45.530
for many centuries found it difficult

31:45.530 --> 31:46.350
to tolerate

31:46.910 --> 31:48.790
not only other religions

31:48.790 --> 31:51.570
but even deviant forms of their own.

31:52.250 --> 31:53.350
In the medieval Muslim

31:53.350 --> 31:55.410
states on the other hand, there was

31:55.410 --> 31:57.690
an acceptance of diversity.

31:58.650 --> 31:59.490
The Quran itself

31:59.870 --> 32:01.450
says there is

32:01.450 --> 32:03.210
no constraint in religion.

32:04.390 --> 32:05.890
A German scholar has recently

32:05.890 --> 32:07.470
argued that this is not a plea for

32:07.470 --> 32:09.410
tolerance but an expression of resignation.

32:10.630 --> 32:11.510
That is not how it was

32:11.510 --> 32:12.370
generally understood.

32:15.310 --> 32:17.470
There is also a saying attributed to

32:17.470 --> 32:18.090
the prophet,

32:19.370 --> 32:21.610
difference of opinion among my people

32:21.610 --> 32:23.030
is a blessing from God.

32:24.210 --> 32:24.670
Again,

32:25.730 --> 32:27.010
an argument that diversity,

32:27.270 --> 32:29.190
that pluralism are good things

32:29.190 --> 32:30.150
in themselves.

32:31.130 --> 32:33.190
This tolerance was of course limited.

32:34.010 --> 32:34.870
It did not mean

32:34.870 --> 32:37.330
as some modern apologists would have it

32:37.330 --> 32:39.170
the granting of equal rights

32:39.170 --> 32:41.650
of citizenship to non-Muslims.

32:41.750 --> 32:43.170
That would have been seen

32:43.170 --> 32:44.170
not as a merit

32:44.170 --> 32:46.970
but as a dereliction of duty.

32:47.230 --> 32:48.490
It is obviously absurd

32:48.490 --> 32:50.070
to give equal rights

32:50.070 --> 32:53.190
to those who reject it.

32:55.850 --> 32:57.330
Nevertheless, there was

32:57.330 --> 32:59.110
a very real tolerance

32:59.110 --> 33:01.750
allowed to non-Muslim communities

33:01.750 --> 33:03.890
and even a much more

33:03.890 --> 33:04.910
searching test,

33:05.430 --> 33:07.530
even deviant Muslim communities.

33:09.110 --> 33:11.770
One does not find heresy hunts

33:11.770 --> 33:13.210
and inquisitions

33:13.210 --> 33:15.570
in Islamic history except

33:15.570 --> 33:17.550
on very rare and exceptional

33:17.550 --> 33:18.450
circumstances.

33:20.270 --> 33:23.070
In most of the Muslim states,

33:23.550 --> 33:25.190
Muslims of different branches

33:25.190 --> 33:27.390
of the faith, Christians

33:27.390 --> 33:29.210
of different churches, Jews

33:29.210 --> 33:30.670
lived side by side.

33:31.390 --> 33:33.170
Now, this was limited

33:33.170 --> 33:35.570
tolerance, but it was

33:35.570 --> 33:36.810
much more extensive

33:36.810 --> 33:39.210
in one sense than what is

33:39.210 --> 33:41.210
accorded to minorities of the present time.

33:41.930 --> 33:43.110
And this gives rise

33:43.110 --> 33:44.750
to one of the difficulties

33:44.750 --> 33:46.970
of the accommodation

33:46.970 --> 33:49.290
of Muslim minorities in

33:49.290 --> 33:51.070
Christian or post-Christian states

33:51.070 --> 33:53.530
in Europe and elsewhere at the present

33:53.530 --> 33:55.550
time. Muslims

33:55.550 --> 33:57.290
naturally expect

33:57.290 --> 33:59.430
the same tolerance from

33:59.430 --> 34:01.470
Christian governments as they

34:01.470 --> 34:03.710
in the past gave to Christian

34:03.710 --> 34:05.690
minorities in Muslim countries.

34:06.570 --> 34:07.470
What they are in fact

34:07.470 --> 34:09.630
getting is much more than that

34:09.630 --> 34:11.630
but also much less

34:11.630 --> 34:12.330
than that.

34:14.130 --> 34:15.930
The status of a tolerated

34:15.930 --> 34:17.570
minority under Muslim rule

34:17.570 --> 34:19.810
carried with it a very

34:19.810 --> 34:21.950
large measure of internal autonomy.

34:23.990 --> 34:25.730
The Christian Ecclesiastical

34:25.730 --> 34:27.610
Authorities had real and

34:27.610 --> 34:29.130
enforceable jurisdiction

34:29.130 --> 34:30.490
over the faithful.

34:32.130 --> 34:33.370
They administered

34:33.370 --> 34:35.970
their own laws and adjudicated

34:35.970 --> 34:37.630
cases in their own tribunals.

34:37.650 --> 34:38.990
The same was true of the Jews.

34:39.570 --> 34:40.930
So that in the same street

34:41.440 --> 34:43.590
if you had, shall we

34:43.590 --> 34:45.770
say, a

34:45.770 --> 34:47.630
Muslim, an Orthodox

34:47.630 --> 34:49.490
Christian, a Catholic Christian and a

34:49.490 --> 34:51.470
Jew, they would be subject to

34:51.470 --> 34:52.930
four different systems of law.

34:53.750 --> 34:55.850
If they died, their estates

34:55.850 --> 34:57.430
would be divided according to four

34:57.430 --> 34:59.250
different systems of inheritance law

34:59.250 --> 35:01.510
and so on and so on. Even to

35:01.510 --> 35:03.150
some extent criminal jurisdiction.

35:04.570 --> 35:05.750
Let me quote one

35:05.750 --> 35:07.710
example and an important one.

35:08.150 --> 35:09.390
The question of polygamy

35:09.390 --> 35:10.430
and concubinage.

35:11.550 --> 35:13.510
Muslim law permits both polygamy

35:13.510 --> 35:15.350
and concubinage.

35:15.850 --> 35:17.550
Jewish law in the Islamic lands,

35:17.610 --> 35:19.390
though not in the Christian lands, permits

35:19.390 --> 35:21.730
polygamy but not concubinage.

35:22.070 --> 35:23.510
Christian law of all churches

35:23.510 --> 35:25.810
at all times prohibits both polygamy

35:25.810 --> 35:27.090
and concubinage.

35:27.810 --> 35:29.410
It was therefore possible for

35:29.410 --> 35:31.490
rabbinic and Christian

35:31.490 --> 35:33.490
church authorities to

35:33.490 --> 35:35.650
punish people and sometimes punish

35:35.650 --> 35:37.730
them severely for offenses

35:37.730 --> 35:39.630
which were not offenses at all

35:39.630 --> 35:41.490
according to the law of the land, the

35:41.490 --> 35:43.030
dominant community in the land

35:43.030 --> 35:45.490
or breaches of the marriage laws.

35:47.270 --> 35:47.850
They

35:47.850 --> 35:49.950
controlled their own educational systems.

35:50.030 --> 35:51.810
They had their own schools in which they taught

35:51.810 --> 35:53.970
whatever they wanted to teach, provided

35:53.970 --> 35:56.150
only that it was not subversive

35:56.150 --> 35:58.190
and even that was not very rigorously

35:58.190 --> 35:58.730
enforced.

36:00.510 --> 36:01.790
One understands then

36:01.790 --> 36:03.890
that Muslims who come to Europe

36:03.890 --> 36:06.070
have a different notion

36:06.070 --> 36:07.850
of minority rights

36:07.850 --> 36:09.130
and minority status

36:09.670 --> 36:11.230
and a different expectation.

36:11.910 --> 36:13.990
These minorities in principle had no

36:13.990 --> 36:16.090
political rights. They were not

36:16.090 --> 36:18.650
supposed to participate in any way

36:18.650 --> 36:19.910
in the conduct of government.

36:20.510 --> 36:22.170
They were, with insignificant

36:22.170 --> 36:24.250
exceptions, excluded from

36:24.250 --> 36:26.270
the bearing of arms or from any form of

36:26.270 --> 36:28.190
military service. In fact

36:28.190 --> 36:30.310
they did sometimes participate in

36:30.310 --> 36:32.430
politics but always in a relatively

36:32.430 --> 36:33.770
subordinate capacity.

36:34.490 --> 36:35.790
Here, the other side.

36:37.550 --> 36:38.130
This

36:38.130 --> 36:39.650
degree of tolerance

36:39.650 --> 36:42.050
is of course no longer

36:42.050 --> 36:43.970
acceptable by modern standards

36:43.970 --> 36:46.070
and it broke down in the

36:46.070 --> 36:48.170
19th century when

36:48.170 --> 36:50.150
the non-Muslim subjects

36:50.150 --> 36:51.870
of the Ottoman Empire and of other

36:51.870 --> 36:54.030
Muslim states were no longer

36:54.030 --> 36:56.350
satisfied with the

36:56.350 --> 36:57.910
tolerated and subordinate

36:57.910 --> 37:00.070
status accorded to them by the old

37:00.070 --> 37:01.890
laws. They demanded

37:01.890 --> 37:03.890
emancipation, they demanded equal

37:03.890 --> 37:06.130
rights and so on. The old system

37:06.130 --> 37:08.090
broke down. It has not

37:08.090 --> 37:09.530
been adequately replaced.

37:10.350 --> 37:11.950
Nevertheless, I think one should remember

37:11.950 --> 37:14.030
that for a long time the

37:14.030 --> 37:15.950
Muslim world was far more

37:15.950 --> 37:18.310
tolerant than Christian

37:18.310 --> 37:19.230
countries.

37:20.550 --> 37:22.110
Nowadays we tend to

37:22.910 --> 37:24.110
measure tolerance by

37:24.110 --> 37:25.410
the movement of refugees

37:25.950 --> 37:27.790
and intolerance rather

37:27.790 --> 37:29.430
by the movement of refugees

37:29.950 --> 37:32.330
from persecuting authorities

37:32.330 --> 37:33.550
to free authorities.

37:34.170 --> 37:35.930
We should bear in mind that until the

37:35.930 --> 37:37.990
16th and 17th centuries the movement

37:37.990 --> 37:40.230
of refugees was almost entirely

37:40.230 --> 37:41.690
isolated from Christendom to Islam,

37:42.330 --> 37:44.250
not only of Jews but even

37:44.250 --> 37:45.430
of deviant Christians.

37:46.730 --> 37:48.650
In 16th and 17th century

37:48.650 --> 37:50.110
Istanbul, for example,

37:50.730 --> 37:52.190
there were Protestants from Catholic

37:52.190 --> 37:53.910
countries, Catholics from Protestant

37:53.910 --> 37:55.970
countries and Jews from both

37:55.970 --> 37:58.210
enjoying the relatively free

37:58.210 --> 38:00.070
air of the Turkish Muslim capital.

38:05.030 --> 38:05.070
The

38:05.730 --> 38:06.630
economic point

38:06.630 --> 38:08.090
is again I think an important one.

38:08.090 --> 38:10.450
We tend nowadays to think of

38:10.450 --> 38:12.090
the Islamic world as

38:13.590 --> 38:14.530
irretrievably

38:14.530 --> 38:16.510
feudal and therefore

38:16.710 --> 38:18.630
opposed to free market

38:18.630 --> 38:20.870
and other forms of capitalist

38:20.870 --> 38:21.690
enterprise.

38:22.590 --> 38:24.410
This is a

38:24.410 --> 38:26.070
reversal of the historical

38:26.070 --> 38:26.670
sequence.

38:28.110 --> 38:30.110
In the West the classical sequence

38:30.110 --> 38:31.710
is of course slavery,

38:34.030 --> 38:34.510
feudalism,

38:35.050 --> 38:35.590
capitalism.

38:35.590 --> 38:37.970
But the Islamic history is not

38:37.970 --> 38:39.850
Marxist. It doesn't follow the Marxist

38:39.850 --> 38:40.330
rule.

38:47.290 --> 38:49.590
It is of course slavery,

38:52.310 --> 38:53.710
feudalism, capitalism.

38:54.590 --> 38:56.110
But the Islamic history is not

38:56.110 --> 38:57.990
Marxist. It doesn't follow the Marxist

38:57.990 --> 38:58.450
rule.

39:23.030 --> 39:23.830
These

39:23.830 --> 39:24.510
matters were

39:24.510 --> 39:26.090
debated intensely

39:26.090 --> 39:27.890
and we have expressions of different

39:27.890 --> 39:28.270
views.

39:28.970 --> 39:30.410
The question, for example, of

39:30.410 --> 39:32.630
price fixing versus

39:32.630 --> 39:33.570
market forces

39:33.570 --> 39:35.570
was hotly debated rather

39:35.570 --> 39:37.730
than a thousand years ago in

39:37.730 --> 39:39.690
Baghdad and Damascus and other cities of

39:39.690 --> 39:40.390
the Middle East.

39:41.330 --> 39:43.710
They quote a saying attributed to the

39:43.710 --> 39:45.530
prophet, only God

39:45.530 --> 39:47.050
can fix prices.

39:49.030 --> 39:49.650
An eloquent

39:49.650 --> 39:51.470
theological formulation of laisse

39:51.470 --> 39:51.850
faire.

39:54.190 --> 39:55.210
Another saying

39:55.210 --> 39:57.590
is that he

39:57.590 --> 39:59.730
who earns money is the friend of God.

40:01.030 --> 40:01.970
Another saying

40:01.970 --> 40:03.550
the honest

40:03.550 --> 40:05.650
merchant who is killed

40:05.650 --> 40:06.630
is a martyr.

40:07.610 --> 40:09.690
In other words, counts as a martyr for the

40:09.690 --> 40:10.110
faith.

40:13.210 --> 40:15.510
The importance of the commercial

40:15.510 --> 40:17.330
development of medieval

40:17.330 --> 40:19.550
Islam is

40:21.430 --> 40:23.390
recorded even by the vocabulary

40:23.390 --> 40:25.430
which we use in European languages

40:25.430 --> 40:28.030
at a time when feudal Europe

40:28.030 --> 40:29.470
was a rather

40:29.470 --> 40:31.610
impoverished primitive

40:31.610 --> 40:33.610
outpost on the

40:34.150 --> 40:35.510
wild northwest frontier

40:35.510 --> 40:36.810
of the Islamic world.

40:37.210 --> 40:39.190
Think, for example, of how many Muslim words,

40:39.490 --> 40:41.170
how many Arabic or Persian words

40:41.170 --> 40:43.850
there are in our commercial vocabulary.

40:44.450 --> 40:45.030
Tariff

40:45.480 --> 40:46.190
is Arabic.

40:48.470 --> 40:49.710
The Italian dogana,

40:49.850 --> 40:51.750
the French douane, come from the Spanish

40:51.750 --> 40:53.450
adwana which come from the perso

40:53.450 --> 40:54.410
Arabic diwan.

40:55.130 --> 40:57.310
Czech is Persian and one could add

40:57.310 --> 40:58.250
many others

40:58.250 --> 41:01.830
which came from a

41:01.830 --> 41:02.970
financially and economically

41:02.970 --> 41:04.490
more advanced society

41:04.490 --> 41:06.190
to a more primitive one.

41:08.950 --> 41:10.490
The change there, as I said,

41:10.990 --> 41:12.470
reversed the Marxist sequence,

41:13.790 --> 41:14.470
a point which

41:14.470 --> 41:16.030
Marx seems to have overlooked.

41:19.270 --> 41:19.790
With

41:19.790 --> 41:22.210
uncharacteristic humility, he did

41:22.210 --> 41:24.250
recognize that the canonical

41:24.250 --> 41:26.390
western sequence didn't apply

41:26.390 --> 41:28.770
to other societies

41:28.770 --> 41:31.030
and he met that by inventing

41:31.030 --> 41:32.730
the Asiatic mode of production

41:32.730 --> 41:34.630
which presumably covers everything

41:34.630 --> 41:36.150
from Anatolia to Japan.

41:38.070 --> 41:39.810
The feudal age

41:40.730 --> 41:42.590
of the Islamic economy

41:42.590 --> 41:44.290
has lasted for a very long time

41:44.290 --> 41:46.230
but there again there is an earlier

41:46.230 --> 41:48.570
tradition to which one can look

41:48.570 --> 41:50.610
back with, I think,

41:52.030 --> 41:52.430
elements

41:52.430 --> 41:54.730
conducive to a better development.

41:56.390 --> 41:58.850
Let me, before ending,

41:59.570 --> 42:00.270
refer to

42:34.170 --> 42:34.410
a

42:55.590 --> 42:55.830
a

42:55.830 --> 42:55.950
a

42:55.950 --> 42:55.970
a

42:55.970 --> 42:55.990
a

43:03.690 --> 43:03.770
a

43:03.770 --> 43:03.810
a

43:25.290 --> 43:25.370
a

43:25.370 --> 43:25.510
a

43:25.510 --> 43:25.530
a

43:25.530 --> 43:25.550
a

43:25.550 --> 43:25.590
a

